      • openStream

        public java.io.InputStream openStream()
                               throws java.io.IOException
        Opens a new InputStream to read from the zip entry associated with this ZipVirtualFile instance.

        It is important to invoke InputStream.close() when the returned stream is no longer needed.

        Please note, there are conditions that this will throw IllegalArgumentException as well as the specified IOException.

        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • setBatchMode

        public void setBatchMode​(boolean b)
                  throws java.io.IOException
        Batch mode should be activated when repeated, uninterrupted access is required to one or more of the entries (via openStream() in the source zip file. This keeps the underlying file pointer open and will reduce the time required to open streams.

        It is important to deactivate batch mode when no longer required to ensure that this instance becomes eligible for garbage collection.

        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
